column168: REICHHHOLD SHIPPED 88 DRUMS OF WASTE FLAMMABLE LIQUID TO PETRO-CHEM.  HAZMA T, AS CARRIER DELIVERED THE SHIPMENT DIRECTLY TO PETRO-CHEM ON 3/2/86 WITHO UT INCIDENT.  PETRO-CHEM SAMPLED ALL DRUMS WHILE STILL ON HAZMAT'S VEHICLE AND UNLOADED ONLY 29 DRUMS; REJECTING THE REMAINING 59 BECAUSE THEY WERE "S OLID" (AS NOTED IN ITEM 19 ON MANIFEST).  HAZMAT'S DRIVER WAS INSTRUCTED TO RETURN THE "REJECTED" 59 DRUMS TO REICHHOLD.  WHILE ENROUTE BACK TO NIAGAR A FALLS, NY THE VEHICLE STOPPED FOR A MECHANICAL CHECK AND THE DRIVER NOTIC ED A SLOW DRIPPAGE OF MATERIAL FROM THE VAN.  UPON OPERNING THE TRAILER HE DISCOVERED ABOUT 30 DRUMS HAD LIQUID ON THEIR TOPS.  THE LIQUID HAD ESCAPED FROM THE DRUMS DUE TO LOOSE BUNGS.  PETRO-CHEM PERSONNEL AFTER SAMPLING TH E CONTAINERS, NEVER TIGHTENED THE BUNGS BEFORE INSTRUCTING THE DRIVER TO LEAVE. IN ADDITION,, A FEW 17H DRUMS LEAKED AROUND THE COVER GASKETS. BOTH THE SHIPPER AND CONSIGNEE HAVE BEEN ADVISED OF THE LOOSE FITTINGS. DUE TO EARLY DISCOVERY OF THE PROBLEM, VERY LITTLE MATERIAL HAD LEAKED (APPROX. 20 GALLONS). HAZMAT PERSONNEL TIGHTENED ALL BUNGS, ABSORBED THE LIQUID ON CLAY ABSORBENTS AND SHOVELED UP ALL CONTAMINATED DIRT. CONTAMINATED ABSORBENTS AND DIRT WERE PLACED IN THREE (3) 17H DRUMS. THESE MATERIAL WILL BE LAND- FILLED IN A CHEMICAL SECURE LANDFILL FACILITY AS HAZARDOUS WASTE IN ACCORD- ANCE WITH USEPA REGULATIONS AS SOON AS ARRANGEMENTS WITH QUALIFIED LANDFILL ARE COMPLETED. PLEASE NOTE THAT HAZMAT AS TRANSPORTER #1 DELIVERED THE SHIPMENT DIRECTLY TO THE DESIGNATED DISPOSAL FACILITY. HAZMAT CAN NOT EXPLAIN WHY TIMOTHY TILOTTI, A REPRESENTATIVE OF PETRO-CHEM ALSO SIGNED AS TRANSPORTER #2 AND FILLED IN SOLVENT DISTILLERS, INC. IN ITEM 7 AS TRANS- PORTER #2. THERE WAS NO TRANSPORTER #2 INVOLVED IN THIS SHIPMENT.

column168: THE RELEASE OF APPROXIMATELY ONE QUART OF ISO-BUTANOL OCCURRED AS THE DRUM OF PACKAGED WASTE MATERIAL (WITH VERMICULTIE ABSORBENT) WAS BEING TRANSFERR ED FROM TRUCK TO TRUCK BY A FORKLIFT.  THE DRUM WAS PLACED ON A PALLET TO B E MOVED.  WHEN THE FORKLIFT HIT A SMALL BUMP THE DRUM FELL OFF ONTO ITS SID E.  AT THAT POINT A SMALL AMOUNT OF LIQUID (ONE QUART) WAS NOTICED TO HAVE LEAKED FROM ALONG THE LID OF THE DRUM.  A SMALL BAG OF CONTAMINATED SOIL WA S IMMEDIATELY CLEANED UP AND PLACED IN THE DRUM WITH THE OTHER WASTE MATERI ALS TO BE SHIPPED FOR DISPOSAL AT A CHEMICALLY SECURE LANDFILL.  THE PROBAB LE CAUSE COULD BE ATTRIBUTED TO A COMBINATION OF CIRCUMSTANCES.  OBVIOUSLY, THE SHOCK OF THE DRUM FALLING AND LYING ON ITS SIDE WAS THE MOST IMMEDIATE CAUSE, BUT ALSO THEY WAY IN WHICH THE INNER GLASS BOTTLES WERE PACKAGED HA D SOME EFFECT.  IF THE BOTTLES WERE PACKAGED WITH THE BOTTLES TOO CLOSE TO EACH OTHER OR TO THE SIDE OF THE STEEL DRUM A SUFFICIENT JOLT MAY CAUSE THE BOTTLE TO BREAK.  ALL FIELD PERSONNEL PACKAGING AND HANDLING MATERIALS WER E BRIEFED ON PACKAGING MATERIALS WITH SUFFICIENT CUSHIONING AROUND THEM TO PREVENT ANY FUTURE INCIDENTS.

column168: 2 BOTTLES INSIDE CARTON DAMAGED AND BROKEN.

PACKAGE WAS BEING MOVED FORM CART TO TRAILER, LOADER (JAMES KISSENTANER) TR IPED AND DROPPED PACKAGE.  LIQUID STARTED LEAKING FROM BOX, LOADER NOTIFIED ME (KEVIN DILDAY, TERMINAL MANAGER) ON VISUAL INSPECTION I COULD NOT DETER MINE CONTENTS DUE TO NO DOT MARKINGS OR LABELING AND UN OR NA NUMBERS.  I C ONCLUDED FROM THE SMELL OF THE LIQUID I COULD TELL IT WAS POSSIBLY HAZARDOU S AREA WAS EVACUATED ADN OIL DRY WAS USED TO CONTAIN LIQUID BY MAKING DIKES .  DALLAS FIRE DEPT. WAS CALLED.  THEY ARRIVED ON THE SCENE, REMOVED BROKEN BOTTLE FROM BOX; DETERMINED IT WAS ALCOHOL N.O.S. VERIFIED THAT IT WAS NOT A THREAT TO THE ENVIRONMENT AND CONCLUDED BY SAYING WE HAD DONE THE RIGHT THINGS AND THAT WASTE COULD BE DISPOSED OF.  IN CONCLUDING INVESTIGATION IT WAS DETERMINED THAT THE MATERIAL HAD BEEN SHIPPED OUT CORRECTLY BUT, HAD 3 OTHER GALLONS SHIPPED WITH IT.  ORIGINAL BOX WAS DAMAGED BY TEX-PACK EXPRE SS 2001 IRVING DALLAS, TX. 75207 AND RESHIPPED IN A DIFFERENT BOX.  I HAVE NOTIFIED TOM SIGLEY WITH TEX-PACK CONCERNING REPACKAGING OF HAZARDOUS MATER IALS.  HE STATED THAT HE WOULD NOTIFY RESPONSIBLE PARTIES.
